font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt;" =
class=3D""><span style=3D"font-size: 11pt;" class=3D"">&lt;</span><a =
href=3D"http://sigir.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/p036.pdf" class=3D"" =
style=3D"font-size: 11pt; color: =
purple;">http://sigir.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/p036.pdf</a><span =
style=3D"font-size: 11pt;" class=3D"">&gt;.</span></div><div =
style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; margin: 0cm =
0cm 0.0001pt;" class=3D""><span lang=3D"EN-US" class=3D""><o:p =
class=3D"">&nbsp;</o:p></span></div><div style=3D"font-size: 11pt; =
font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt;" =
class=3D""><span lang=3D"EN-US" class=3D"">This workshop will be =
relevant to scholars in computer and information science, specialized in =
IR, bibliometrics and NLP. The Shared Task is expected to be of interest =
to a broad community including those working in CL and NLP, especially =
in the sub-disciplines of text summarization, discourse structure in =
scholarly discourse, paraphrase, textual entailment and text =
simplification. The workshop will also be of importance for all =
stakeholders in the publication pipeline: implementers, publishers and =
policymakers. Formal citation metrics are increasingly a factor in =
decision-making by universities and funding bodies worldwide, making the =
need for research in applying these metrics more pressing. Today's =
publishers continue to provide new ways to support their consumers in =
disseminating and retrieving the right published works to their =
audience. Even when only considering the scholarly sites within Computer =
Science, we find that the field is well-represented - ACM Portal, IEEE =
Xplore, Google Scholar, PSU's CiteSeerX, MSR's Academic Search, =
Elsevier=E2=80=99s Mendeley, Tsinghua's ArnetMiner, Trier's DBLP, =
Hiroshima's PRESRI; with this workshop we hope to bring a number of =
these contributors together.<o:p class=3D""></o:p></span></div><div =
style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; margin: 0cm =
0cm 0.0001pt;" class=3D""><span lang=3D"EN-US" class=3D""><br =
class=3D""></span></div><div style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: =
Calibri, sans-serif; margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt;" class=3D""><span =
lang=3D"EN-US" class=3D""><o:p class=3D""></o:p></span></div><div =
style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; margin: 0cm =
0cm 0.0001pt;" class=3D""><span lang=3D"EN-US" class=3D"">=3D=3D=3D =
Workshop Topics =3D=3D=3D<o:p class=3D""></o:p></span></div><div =
style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; margin: 0cm =
0cm 0.0001pt;" class=3D""><span lang=3D"EN-US" class=3D"">We invite =
stimulating as well as unpublished submissions on topics including - but =
not limited to - full-text analysis, multimedia and multilingual =
analysis and alignment as well as the application of citation-based NLP =
or information retrieval and information seeking techniques in digital =
libraries. Specific examples of fields of interests include (but are not =
limited to):<o:p class=3D""></o:p></span></div><div style=3D"font-size: =
11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt;" =
class=3D""><span lang=3D"EN-US" class=3D"">- Infrastructure for =
scientific mining and IR<o:p class=3D""></o:p></span></div><div =
style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; margin: 0cm =
0cm 0.0001pt;" class=3D""><span lang=3D"EN-US" class=3D"">- Semantic and =
Network-based indexing, navigation, searching and browsing in structured =
data<o:p class=3D""></o:p></span></div><div style=3D"font-size: 11pt; =
font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt;" =
class=3D""><span lang=3D"EN-US" class=3D"">- Discourse structure =
identification and argument mining from scientific papers<o:p =
class=3D""></o:p></span></div><div style=3D"font-size: 11pt; =
font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt;" =
class=3D""><span lang=3D"EN-US" class=3D"">- Summarisation and =
question-answering for scholarly DLs<o:p =
class=3D""></o:p></span></div><div style=3D"font-size: 11pt; =
font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt;" =
class=3D""><span lang=3D"EN-US" class=3D"">- Bibliometrics, citation =
analysis and network analysis for IR<o:p =
class=3D""></o:p></span></div><div style=3D"font-size: 11pt; =
font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt;" =
class=3D""><span lang=3D"EN-US" class=3D"">- Task based user modelling, =
interaction, and personalisation<o:p class=3D""></o:p></span></div><div =
style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; margin: 0cm =
0cm 0.0001pt;" class=3D""><span lang=3D"EN-US" class=3D"">- =
Recommendation for scholarly papers, reviewers, citations and =
publication venues<o:p class=3D""></o:p></span></div><div =
style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; margin: 0cm =
0cm 0.0001pt;" class=3D""><span lang=3D"EN-US" class=3D"">- Measurement =
and evaluation of quality and impact<o:p =
class=3D""></o:p></span></div><div style=3D"font-size: 11pt; =
font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt;" =
class=3D""><span lang=3D"EN-US" class=3D"">- Metadata and controlled =
vocabularies for resource description and discovery;<o:p =
class=3D""></o:p></span></div><div style=3D"font-size: 11pt; =
font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt;" =
class=3D""><span lang=3D"EN-US" class=3D"">- Automatic metadata =
discovery, such as language identification<o:p =
class=3D""></o:p></span></div><div style=3D"font-size: 11pt; =
font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt;" =
class=3D""><span lang=3D"EN-US" class=3D"">- Disambiguation issues in =
scholarly DLs using NLP or IR techniques; Data cleaning and data =
quality<o:p class=3D""></o:p></span></div><div style=3D"font-size: 11pt; =
font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt;" =
class=3D""><span lang=3D"EN-US" class=3D""><o:p =
class=3D""></o:p></span></div><div style=3D"font-size: 11pt; =
font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt;" =
class=3D""><span lang=3D"EN-US" class=3D"">For the paper sessions, we =
especially invite descriptions of running projects and ongoing work as =
well as contributions from industry. Papers that investigate multiple =
themes directly are especially welcome.<o:p =
class=3D""></o:p></span></div><div style=3D"font-size: 11pt; =
font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt;" =
class=3D""><span lang=3D"EN-US" class=3D""><br =
class=3D""></span></div><div style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: =
Calibri, sans-serif; margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt;" class=3D""><span =
lang=3D"EN-US" class=3D""><o:p class=3D""></o:p></span></div><div =
style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; margin: 0cm =
0cm 0.0001pt;" class=3D""><span lang=3D"EN-US" class=3D"">=3D=3D=3D =
Submission Details =3D=3D=3D<o:p class=3D""></o:p></span></div><div =
style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; margin: 0cm =
0cm 0.0001pt;" class=3D""><span lang=3D"EN-US" class=3D"">All =
submissions must be written in English following Springer LNCS author =
guidelines (max. 6 pages for short and 12 pages for full papers, =
Springer LNCS: &lt;<a =
href=3D"http://www.springer.com/gp/computer-science/lncs/conference-procee=
dings-guidelines" style=3D"color: purple; text-decoration: underline;" =
class=3D"">http://www.springer.com/gp/computer-science/lncs/conference-pro=
ceedings-guidelines</a>&gt;; exclusive of unlimited pages for =
references) and should be submitted as PDF files to EasyChair. All =
submissions will be reviewed by at least two independent reviewers. =
Please be aware of the fact that at least one author per paper needs to =
register for the workshop and attend the workshop to present the work. =
In case of no-show the paper (even if accepted) will be deleted from the =
proceedings and from the program.<o:p class=3D""></o:p></span></div><div =
style=3D"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; margin: 0cm =
